ey points \u2022 The central lesson learned from every previous economic crisis is that the poorest people in developing countries suffer the most and that not enough is done to help them. Beneath the current crisis lies a \u201cDevelopment Emergency\u201d with catastrophic implications if we fail to respond effectively. \u2022 While there is still uncertainty about the scope and impact of the economic crisis in the region, it is clear that children and women in many Pacific Island countries are likely to be amongst those most severely affected, and that those already most vulnerable will face the greatest impact. The crisis compounds the recent shock from high food and fuel prices.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "40ffad5e-8656-4065-bc14-0241b4979ac6": {"__data__": {"id_": "40ffad5e-8656-4065-bc14-0241b4979ac6", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-pacific-island-children-women-during-economic-and-food-crises", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Protecting Pacific Island Children & Women during Economic and Food Crises", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-pacific-island-children-women-during-economic-and-food-crises", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "5e39fec81ad22c24302f1fc7cba0d33807b7d03cff0004f55c0c9c38d66ccf16"}, "2": {"node_id": "60954fee-9c2b-4532-a5ca-d073047bc4ae", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-pacific-island-children-