of their people, we hope to better equip government o\ufb03cials to ful\ufb01l this role as duty bearers. Civil society also has an extremely key role to play in meeting the Millennium Development Goals. In the Paci\ufb01c, including in the Polynesian sub region, local NGOs and civil society organisations, including faith-based institutions have been very active in advocacy and service delivery in education, health, women\u2019s issues, environment and so on. The Paci\ufb01c has a long tradition of consultation with the people, and it is important that this participatory process is maintained as countries open up the policy and budget debate to allow inputs from civil society. We hope therefore that this workshop will further deepen understanding of the various MDGs and what needs to be done, and that CSOs as right holders will work with Governments to contribute to achievement of the MDGs, holding governments accountable where necessary. I am therefore pleased to note the presence of several NGO and CSO representatives at this workshop, and I extend a particularly warm welcome to all of you. Let me emphasise that this sub regional workshop is not meant to be a one-o\ufb00 event. Rather, it is intended to further increase awareness and develop national capacities in policy, planning and budgeting. Recognising that some countries have developed relatively strong national capacities in some of these areas, we would like to build on this by introducing innovative approaches to planning to achieve national priorities and the MDGs. The workshop will also introduce sectoral costing tools developed by UNDP Regional Centre in Colombo and the UNDP Bureau for Development Policy. These costing tools can support governments to estimate expenditure in education, health, gender, energy, environment, infrastructure and other sectors, and also support prioritisation of interventions and policy options. During the Action Planning session on the last day of the workshop, you will have an opportunity to identify areas where further support is needed at country level so that capacity strengthening and enhancement takes place on an ongoing basis. For Cook Islands, Niue, Samoa and Tokelau I am pleased to announce that UNDP will be placing national Strategic Planners in the Ministries of Planning to support the process of mainstreaming MDGs into national development planning as well as serve as Liaison O\ufb03cers for UNDP and the UNDAF In closing, I would like to thank our colleague in the Government of the Cook Islands for o\ufb00ering to host this sub-regional workshop in Rarotonga, and for their invaluable organizational and logistical support, without which this workshop would not have been possible.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "3514b267-f294-44da-9f71-d5c7e84de935": {"__data__": {"id_": "3514b267-f294-44da-9f71-d5c7e84de935", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/sub-regional-workshop-mdg-based-planning-costing-and-budgeting-polynesian-countries", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Sub Regional Workshop on MDG-based Planning, Costing and Budgeting for the Polynesian Countries", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/sub-regional-workshop-mdg-based-planning-costing-and-budgeting-polynesian-countries", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "c0364f2c330af904a8c60272f5d95f76708fad387c90375e108244a61b6cb741"}, "2": {"node_id": "ed8d6d4c-7d52-48a7-9ca5-27a316c3b0c0", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/sub-regional-workshop-mdg-based-planning-costing-and-budgeting-polynesian-countries", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "0b184162d549766e4ee99478506e48b13d7e27bfc8f293903d6ec262ec85a299"}}, "hash": "ccf1686144b6fb567dc64efabacc0344b5397ae3b88a05226a1af10e01799dd4", "text": "I would especially like to thank colleagues from the UNDP Paci\ufb01c Centre who conceptualized this workshop, provided the substantive content and made the arrangements, especially David, Carol and Mezi. I wish you a very interesting workshop and discussions, and look forward to hearing about the outcomes of the workshop. But I also hope that you will get some time to see this beautiful country. Thank you.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "63d8c74a-2822-4595-9587-9891ce1b4ebf": {"__data__": {"id_": "63d8c74a-2822-4595-9587-9891ce1b4ebf", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/sub-regional-workshop-mdg-based-planning-costing-and-budgeting-western-pacific-countries", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Sub Regional Workshop on MDG-based Planning, Costing and Budgeting for Western Pacific Countries", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/sub-regional-workshop-mdg-based-planning-costing-and-budgeting-western-pacific-countries", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "1822d7cec9d2990880f7642e9f7f9fb82f962336c41e8dc7bb1972c904a1c5bd"}, "3": {"node_id": "4593ed0d-0f5a-4f74-b237-8115a5900807", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/sub-regional-workshop-mdg-based-planning-costing-and-budgeting-western-pacific-countries", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "59a13ba964267970ac66957e256c2ccb0bac5d34b646fd09b703b5b16e0567bf"}}, "hash": "a871428176fb867f9f81d4973a41fefe34c7e10f16d6835d25596bd417c59f52", "text": "Sub Regional Workshop on MGD-based Planning, Costing and Budgeting for Western Pacific Countries 12-15 November 2007, Honiara, Solomon Islands 1. Sub Regional Workshop on MDG-based planning, costing and budgeting for Western Paci\ufb01 c countries Introduction As part of the UNDP Pacific Centre\u2019s efforts to strengthen national capacities for countries to comply with the 2005 World Summit Outcome on \u201cCommitment by all developing countries to adopt national plans for achieving the Millennium Development Goals\u201d, in early October 2006, a one-week regional workshop on MDG- based Planning and the Development of a Pro-poor Policy and Budgeting Framework was held in Nadi, Fiji. Organised by the UNDP Pacific Centre, in collaboration with UN and other regional organisation partners, the workshop brought together about 100 government participants from 15 Pacific Islands Countries, as well as UN colleagues. The objective was to strengthen the capacities of government counterparts (Ministries of Finance, Ministries of Planning, Ministries of Women, National Statistics Offices, sector Ministries) and UN staff in the areas of MDG-based planning, pro-poor policies and budgeting, following a gender-sensitive approach. As follow up to that regional workshop, sub regional workshops are being organised to focus on countries\u2019 specific priorities and needs. In this regard, a sub regional workshop was organised for the North Pacific countries (FSM, Marshall Islands, Palau and Kiribati) in June 2007. The second sub regional workshop was organised for Fiji, Vanuatu, Solomon Islands, Nauru and Tuvalu from 12-15 November 2007 in Solomon Islands. Organised by the UNDP Pacific Centre in collaboration with UNESCAP, UNFPA, UNICEF, UNDESA, and the UNDP Regional Centre in Colombo, the workshop brought together approximately 60 participants from the Ministries of Finance, Planning, Health, Women and Energy or Environment as well as 2 representatives from civil society organisations from Fiji, Tuvalu, Nauru, Vanuatu and Solomon Islands respectively. A full list of workshop participants is available at Annex I. The workshop was meant to further strengthen planning, costing and budgeting practices in Pacific countries, and at mid-point to the 2015 deadline, focus efforts and resources towards bridging the gaps to reach the MDGs in the next 7 years. The main theme of the workshop was policy, planning, costing and budgeting to achieve the Millennium Development Goals, with a focus on some sectoral issues of relevance to the participating countries. The sub-regional workshop built on the 2006 Regional Workshop, and incorporated lessons learnt from the Nadi and North Pacific workshops both in the process and the content delivered. The objectives of the workshop were to: (a) build upon the foundation established in October 2006 by looking at MDGs and poverty data for progress monitoring and reporting in the five target countries; (b) introduce the planning, needs assessment and costing tools developed by RCC/ BDP and discuss how they can support policy development for the achievement of the MDGs in Small Islands Developing States; (c) strengthen national capacity to implement the MDGs and the Mauritius Strategy in PICs by making the appropriate linkages with national and sectoral plans, budget frameworks including gender responsive budgeting and the Pacific Plan; (d) address the linkages between poverty, energy, environment and climate change in the Pacific, including the need for a national integrated approach in disaster risk reduction; (e) strengthen planning and budget frameworks by reviewing the process of putting together an MDG-Based Plan or National Sustainable Development Strategy, including monitoring and evaluation; 2. Sub Regional Workshop on MDG-based planning, costing and budgeting for Western Paci\ufb01 c countries (f) strengthen the budgeting process at national level including a gender sensitive approach; Official opening of workshop The workshop was officially opened by Ms. Christina Carlson, UNDP Deputy Resident Representative, Solomon Islands. In her opening remarks, Ms. Carlson placed on record UNDP\u2019s appreciation to the Government of Solomon Islands for accepting to host this sub regional meeting on the MDGs. She highlighted that UN Agencies had come together as a truly One UN for the workshop, and that this partnership would also be reflected in the follow up at country level. As 2007 is the mid-point year for achievement of the MDGs, Ms. Carlson stressed the need for both additional resources and actions to accelerate progress towards the MDGs in the next seven years. The full statement is available under Annex II.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "4593ed0d-0f5a-4f74-b237-8115a5900807": {"__data__": {"id_": "4593ed0d-0f5a-4f74-b237-8115a5900807", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/sub-regional-workshop-mdg-based-planning-costing-and-budgeting-western-pacific-countries", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Sub Regional Workshop on MDG-based Planning, Costing and Budge